67.6	Full_Metal_Jacket	Full Metal Jacket	Full Metal Jacket is a 1987 war film produced and directed by Stanley Kubrick. It is an adaptation of the 1979 novel The Short-Timers by Gustav Hasford and stars Matthew Modine, Vincent D'Onofrio, R. Lee Ermey, Arliss Howard and Adam Baldwin. The film follows a platoon of U.S. Marines through their training and the experiences of two of the platoon in the Tet Offensive during the Vietnam War. The film title refers to the full metal jacket bullet used by infantry riflemen.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Full_Metal_Jacket_poster.jpg/220px-Full_Metal_Jacket_poster.jpg
